with the committee stuff
and studying for exams...

47
00:02:12,560 --> 00:02:15,360
No, no, those are only excuses.

48
00:02:15,360 --> 00:02:17,230
I've never forgotten, not even once!

49
00:02:17,230 --> 00:02:20,200
Don't compare me to you!
You only think of playing around!

50
00:02:20,200 --> 00:02:23,040
Or rather, how you phrased it
just now is really irritating.

51
00:02:23,040 --> 00:02:25,610
How do you win those
giveaways, anyway?

52
00:02:25,610 --> 00:02:28,070
In one word: Love!

53
00:02:28,510 --> 00:02:31,580
Fine, I'm a woman with no love!

54
00:02:31,580 --> 00:02:33,380
Well, if you send in a normal postcard,

55
00:02:33,380 --> 00:02:36,150
you'll lose where you otherwise
stood a chance of winning.

56
00:02:36,150 --> 00:02:37,820
How do you write your
postcards, Kona-chan?

57
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:39,720
Oh, I make them to win, of course!

58
00:02:39,720 --> 00:02:41,090
How?

59
00:02:41,090 --> 00:02:43,460
Neat handwriting is the
most basic of fundamentals.

60
00:02:43,460 --> 00:02:45,220
You have to write a postcard
that the choosers

61
00:02:45,220 --> 00:02:47,830
would just want to
get into their hands.

62
00:02:47,830 --> 00:02:48,800
For example?

63
00:02:48,800 --> 00:02:53,800
For example, use a highlighter to
draw a border on the postcard.

64
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:56,370
Oh, that really shows up well.

65
00:02:56,370 --> 00:02:58,540
Furthermore, you add an illustration,

66
00:02:58,540 --> 00:03:00,310
with a motif of the item
that you want to get.

67
00:03:00,310 --> 00:03:01,800
An illustration?

68
00:03:03,210 --> 00:03:05,040
I don't think I can draw very well.

69
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:10,070
People of that sort resort to numbers,
and send in many cards.

70
00:03:11,050 --> 00:03:12,080
I think I can do that.

71
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:15,350
However, even when
you're submitting a lot,

72
00:03:15,350 --> 00:03:16,790
don't use a printer.

73
00:03:16,790 --> 00:03:20,130
You have to make sure to write
each and every one by hand.

74
00:03:20,130 --> 00:03:22,060
And send a hundred at once.

75
00:03:22,060 --> 00:03:23,130
A hundred?!

76
00:03:23,130 --> 00:03:25,160
A hundred is like normal.

77
00:03:25,160 --> 00:03:26,730
That costs a fortune!

78
00:03:26,730 --> 00:03:29,100
It's so that you can
get what you want.

79
00:03:29,100 --> 00:03:31,500
You need both enthusiasm
and investment.

80
00:03:31,500 --> 00:03:34,440
But isn't there a time when
it's cheaper to just buy it?

81
00:03:34,440 --> 00:03:37,570
There are things in this world
that money can't buy.

82
00:03:38,440 --> 00:03:40,580
A hundred postcards...
Do they fit in a mailbox?

83
00:03:40,580 --> 00:03:43,220
You don't put them in all at once,

84
00:03:43,220 --> 00:03:45,850
but you send them in small portions,
a few at a time.

85
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:47,580
And you have to spread it
over several days.

86
00:03:48,750 --> 00:03:51,490
When you have a lot of cards at once,

87
00:03:51,490 --> 00:03:54,190
the chooser might
shove all of them aside.

88
00:03:54,190 --> 00:03:57,330
Well, there are times when it's best
to not be so desperate,

89
00:03:57,330 --> 00:03:59,200
and times when the opposite is true.

90
00:03:59,200 --> 00:04:00,600
Then what should I do?

91
00:04:00,600 --> 00:04:02,170
That's why it's all about love!

92
00:04:02,170 --> 00:04:03,200
Whatever...

93
00:04:03,200 --> 00:04:05,140
In any case, if you want
to win something,

94
00:04:05,140 --> 00:04:08,140
check out free handouts or flyers
folded into newspapers as well,

95
00:04:08,140 --> 00:04:12,210
and apply for something that
doesn't look too popular.

96
00:04:12,210 --> 00:04:14,280
Chances of winning
are pretty high then.

97
00:04:14,280 --> 00:04:15,920
Yeah, I'll try that.

98
00:04:15,920 --> 00:04:17,410
Where's the love in that?

99
00:04:21,220 --> 00:04:25,290
Kagami, Tsukasa... You sure
don't look alike, for being twins.

100
00:04:25,290 --> 00:04:28,830
Oh, we're fraternal twins.

101
00:04:28,830 --> 00:04:31,800
So the difference is more
like ordinary sisters.

102
00:04:31,800 --> 00:04:34,230
Identical twins come from one egg
and really do look alike,

103
00:04:34,230 --> 00:04:37,540
but fraternal twins can be different
in appearance and personality.

104
00:04:37,540 --> 00:04:38,910
I see.

105
00:04:38,910 --> 00:04:42,170
It's true that Tsukasa is so laid-back,
but Kagami is vicious.

106
00:04:42,170 --> 00:04:42,510
- What was that?!

107
00:04:42,510 --> 00:04:43,280
- Oh, how scary.
- What was that?!

108
00:04:43,280 --> 00:04:43,680
- Oh, how scary.

109
00:04:43,680 --> 00:04:45,880
Maybe if we set your hairdo
and ribbons in the same way,

110
00:04:45,880 --> 00:04:48,280
you might look more alike
than we think.

111
00:04:48,280 --> 00:04:49,410
Kona-chan!

112
00:04:49,850 --> 00:04:51,920
No good, it's impossible to put
something cute on you, Kagami.

113
00:04:51,920 --> 00:04:53,850
Shut up! Don't go imagining
something on your own

114
00:04:53,850 --> 00:04:55,690
and saying something rude from it!

115
00:04:55,690 --> 00:04:57,250
Do you have something
like telepathy?

116
00:04:58,290 --> 00:04:59,830
You know, how twins can be far apart,

117
00:04:59,830 --> 00:05:03,330
but somehow they have
the same lifestyle habits

118
00:05:03,330 --> 00:05:06,600
or same taste in the opposite gender,

119
00:05:06,600 --> 00:05:08,970
and even marry other twins and stuff.

120
00:05:08,970 --> 00:05:11,240
That, and like when one is in danger,

121
00:05:11,240 --> 00:05:15,310
the other can sense it from
somewhere completely different.

122
00:05:15,310 --> 00:05:17,440
There are all sorts of strange
phenomenon out there.

123
00:05:17,440 --> 00:05:19,550
So you have telepathy
or something, right?

124
00:05:19,550 --> 00:05:21,250
How about you try it out right now.
Like, beep-beep-beep.

125
00:05:21,250 --> 00:05:23,520
That's just you reading
too much manga.

126
00:05:23,520 --> 00:05:25,220
Mana-Kana, too...

127
00:05:25,220 --> 00:05:26,350
Mana-Kana?

128
00:05:26,350 --> 00:05:29,460
Both of them were saying how
they were slightly different.

129
00:05:29,460 --> 00:05:32,220
Like how Mana's the one
who's really cautious,

130
00:05:32,220 --> 00:05:33,730
and Kana's the one who's optimistic.

131
00:05:33,730 --> 00:05:37,260
And they said their voices were
slightly different when they sing.

132
00:05:37,260 --> 00:05:38,260
That reminds me,

133
00:05:38,260 --> 00:05:42,470
Mana-Kana had always thought
that they were fraternal twins,

134
00:05:42,470 --> 00:05:45,530
but they recently found out that
they actually were identical.

135
00:05:46,210 --> 00:05:47,370
Really?

136
00:05:47,370 --> 00:05:49,210
But is that something to be
so surprised about?

137
00:05:49,210 --> 00:05:53,380
The definition of identical and
fraternal twins changed recently.

138
00:05:53,380 --> 00:05:55,350
That means there's
the possibility that you two

139
00:05:55,350 --> 00:05:57,250
are identical twins as well,
Kagami, Tsukasa...

140
00:05:57,250 --> 00:05:59,310
The similarities between you two...

141
00:06:00,590 --> 00:06:02,690
Both of you like sweets, right?

142
00:06:02,690 --> 00:06:04,290
Yeah, I love them.

143
00:06:04,290 --> 00:06:05,020
Sort of.

144
00:06:05,020 --> 00:06:06,690
Both of you are left-handed.

145
00:06:06,690 --> 00:06:07,360
- Yeah.

146
00:06:07,360 --> 00:06:07,690
- That's right.
- Yeah.

147
00:06:07,690 --> 00:06:08,460
- That's right.

148
00:06:08,460 --> 00:06:09,730
What's your favorite color?

149
00:06:09,730 --> 00:06:10,630
White, I guess.

150
00:06:10,630 --> 00:06:11,360
- Black.

151
00:06:11,360 --> 00:06:11,630
- The same colors as your souls.
- Black.

152
